Hmm... I'm not good at these small tasks... I'm clumsy just
like that child...

\SE[2] (Mom, you're really focused... I have to make sure
not to disturb you.)

Cough... cough...! There are so many people feeling
unwell... I hope it's not some strange epidemic...

Hey there, miss. Your work is delicate, so I mustn't disturb
you, okay?

The villager who taught me the procedure fell ill... Hmm...
It feels somewhat uneasy...

*cough*... *cough*... Just a little more and I'll finish my
quota. *cough*... I wonder what I should use the money
for...

Cough... I was planning to play once I received the money,
but honestly, I really want to take a break for a while...
Cough...

\SE[4]I feel like the village has changed a little...
\SE[3]...Or maybe it's just my imagination.

\SE[1]Um... I wonder if Aisha's house... is open? It's a
tool shop, but...

I'm keeping watch so that no one slacks off. With the
decrease in manpower, we'll have to make up for it.

\SE[2]Is there something strange about the color of the
ground...? \SE[3]I wonder what this is...

It seems like there are more people taking time off, so we
have a bit of extra space. I wonder if now is the time to
make some profit...?

We store the finished refined stones there. No one except
authorized personnel is allowed to enter, okay?

For a while, lunchtime will be closed. We will be open as
usual in the evening. ... is written.

I'm not feeling well, so I'll be taking a break for a while.
...there's a sign posted.

Cough... Cough... The water is getting cold this season... I
need to finish before it gets really cold...

With the success of the 'Stone Washing' technique and the
increase in staff, the inn is thriving and making a lot of
money...
Cough... cough...! I might have worked a bit too much...

Aisha has a Sable Norwal that she keeps as a pet... It seems
a little lonely because there is no one to play with...
Should I pet it for her?
Cats seem to have no interest in humans at all.

If there's any trouble, please let me know. At that time, I
will fight as a soldier.

Ah... Vita. I'm sorry. I'm not feeling well, so I can't play
with you. Let's play together when I feel better, okay?

It seems like more people are falling ill during this change
of season.... Should I brew some medicinal herbs for
them.... \*cough*... \*cough*....

My skin has become rough from all the water work... With
this, my marriage prospects will be put on hold. *cough*...
*cough*...!
